    • setApplicationFeePercent

      public PaymentLinkCreateParams.Builder setApplicationFeePercent(BigDecimal applicationFeePercent)
      A non-negative decimal between 0 and 100, with at most two decimal places. This represents the percentage of the subscription invoice total that will be transferred to the application owner's Stripe account. There must be at least 1 line item with a recurring price to use this field.

    • setPaymentMethodCollection

      public PaymentLinkCreateParams.Builder setPaymentMethodCollection(PaymentLinkCreateParams.PaymentMethodCollection paymentMethodCollection)
      Specify whether Checkout should collect a payment method. When set to if_required, Checkout will not collect a payment method when the total due for the session is 0.This may occur if the Checkout Session includes a free trial or a discount.

      Can only be set in subscription mode. Defaults to always.

      If you'd like information on how to collect a payment method outside of Checkout, read the guide on configuring subscriptions with a free trial.
